dct_title_s: 1:250,000, 1:250,000 (AMS N502), Sheet Ni41 (AMS N502), Western Siberia
dct_description_sm: Scale: 1:250000;  Projection: transverse mercator;  Relief Symbology: contours, shading, form lines;  Map Type: Topographic maps;  Other Descriptive Notes about Map Series:   Issued in quadrangles of 1₂ of latitude by 2-3₂ of longitude. Set includes various issues of some sheets.  Transverse Mercator projection.  Relief indicated variously by contours, form lines, shading, and spot heights.  Coordinated with series N501, Eastern Europe and N503, Central Siberia.  Each sheet includes Glossary and Location diagram.  Some sheets have city maps on versos.  Accompanied by index map on 2 sheets 27 x 41-51 cm.
